OL,3,CTeenagers' deaths in bike crash led to
OL,4,Crioting against police, court hears
OL,6,F"The hostility grew, very many in the
OL,7,Fcrowd became openly aggressive, openly
OL,8,Fdoing what they could to stir up
OL,9,Ftrouble," Mr Cobbe said.
OL,11,F"The lines held firm until it was
OL,12,Fnecessary to push back. During those
OL,13,Fearly stages the officers did not have
OL,14,Fthe benefit of protective clothing or
OL,15,Fshields. Despite the sneering and
OL,16,Fjeering, the threats and violence, the
OL,17,Fbricks and bottles thrown, they kept
OL,18,Ftheir lines.
